WEBVTT

00:00:02.218 --> 00:00:05.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome to JW Broadcasting®.

00:00:05.689 --> 00:00:08.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
This month, we’ll discuss something

00:00:08.258 --> 00:00:12.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s easy to talk about but difficult to do

00:00:12.629 --> 00:00:15.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
—making wise decisions.

00:00:15.465 --> 00:00:19.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll hear what wise choices
Greg and Joren Harris made

00:00:19.069 --> 00:00:21.471 line:90% position:50% align:center
as they raised their children.

00:00:21.471 --> 00:00:24.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll also catch up with Enrique Torres,

00:00:24.140 --> 00:00:27.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
a man who made great changes in his life,

00:00:27.744 --> 00:00:32.115 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’ll learn what helped him
stick to those changes.

00:00:32.115 --> 00:00:35.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the latest episode of <i>Iron Sharpens Iron</i>

00:00:35.351 --> 00:00:39.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
will show us
how to be adaptable in our ministry.

00:00:39.522 --> 00:00:44.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is JW Broadcasting for April 2023!

00:01:03.079 --> 00:01:05.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
The theme of this month’s program

00:01:05.215 --> 00:01:08.418 line:10% position:50% align:center
is “Make Wise Decisions.”

00:01:08.418 --> 00:01:13.423 line:10% position:50% align:center
And our discussion is based on Job 34:11.

00:01:13.423 --> 00:01:15.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read that together:

00:01:16.392 --> 00:01:19.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For he [Jehovah] will reward a man

00:01:19.462 --> 00:01:21.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
“according to what he does

00:01:21.798 --> 00:01:26.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
and bring upon him
the consequences of his ways.”

00:01:28.204 --> 00:01:30.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
As highlighted in this scripture,

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:33.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
our actions are very important.

00:01:33.576 --> 00:01:36.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
And our actions are usually the result

00:01:36.045 --> 00:01:38.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
of decisions we make.

00:01:38.481 --> 00:01:42.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some decisions are made
after a lot of serious thought.

00:01:42.919 --> 00:01:46.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
Others, though, are made very quickly.

00:01:46.389 --> 00:01:50.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
But no matter how much thought
goes into making a decision,

00:01:50.326 --> 00:01:53.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
we need to recognize this basic fact:

00:01:54.197 --> 00:01:59.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wise decisions bring positive rewards,

00:01:59.135 --> 00:02:04.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
and wrong decisions can result
in very negative consequences.

00:02:05.708 --> 00:02:08.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, all of us
want to make wise decisions.

00:02:08.845 --> 00:02:12.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what are wise decisions?

00:02:12.348 --> 00:02:17.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wise decisions are those
that please our heavenly Father, Jehovah.

00:02:19.022 --> 00:02:22.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
Most of us have already made
some very good decisions.

00:02:22.659 --> 00:02:25.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
These include the big decisions in life,

00:02:25.061 --> 00:02:28.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as dedicating ourselves to Jehovah

00:02:28.131 --> 00:02:30.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
and getting baptized

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:32.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
and deciding not to become involved

00:02:32.268 --> 00:02:35.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the religious and political disputes
of this world.

00:02:36.673 --> 00:02:40.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
No doubt,
before we made those major decisions,

00:02:40.143 --> 00:02:42.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
we spent a lot of time praying about them

00:02:42.912 --> 00:02:45.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
and seeking Jehovah’s direction.

00:02:45.915 --> 00:02:48.384 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’ve seen his blessing in our lives

00:02:48.384 --> 00:02:50.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
because of these right decisions.

00:02:51.521 --> 00:02:53.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this program, though,

00:02:53.523 --> 00:02:57.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
we won’t be discussing such major decisions.

00:02:57.560 --> 00:03:00.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
Rather, we’ll focus on decisions

00:03:00.797 --> 00:03:04.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
that may be viewed by some as minor.

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:06.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, some of these

00:03:06.703 --> 00:03:09.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
can lead to very serious consequences.

00:03:10.673 --> 00:03:13.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, we’ll consider a Bible example

00:03:13.209 --> 00:03:15.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
of a person who served Jehovah

00:03:15.778 --> 00:03:19.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
and yet made some wrong decisions
along the way.

00:03:19.983 --> 00:03:22.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll analyze
what caused this faithful servant

00:03:22.986 --> 00:03:24.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make these wrong decisions.

00:03:25.989 --> 00:03:29.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then we’ll consider what we need to do

00:03:29.259 --> 00:03:32.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order to make wise decisions.

00:03:32.395 --> 00:03:35.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
Finally, we’ll consider what we need to do

00:03:35.331 --> 00:03:39.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we realize we’ve already made
an unwise decision.

00:03:40.203 --> 00:03:45.074 line:90% position:50% align:center
So to start, let’s discuss
a faithful servant of Jehovah

00:03:45.074 --> 00:03:48.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
who made some unwise decisions.

00:03:48.845 --> 00:03:51.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
The example we have in mind

00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:53.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
is that of King Jehoshaphat.

00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:57.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
What was Jehovah’s view
of King Jehoshaphat?

00:03:57.587 --> 00:03:59.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see the answer

00:03:59.188 --> 00:04:02.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
at 2 Chronicles chapter 17

00:04:02.525 --> 00:04:04.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
and verses 3 and 4:

00:04:05.862 --> 00:04:08.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehovah continued with Jehoshaphat

00:04:08.898 --> 00:04:13.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
“because he walked
in the former ways of his forefather David

00:04:13.436 --> 00:04:16.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and did not search for the Baals.

00:04:16.406 --> 00:04:19.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For he searched for the God of his father

00:04:19.108 --> 00:04:21.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and followed his commandment

00:04:21.144 --> 00:04:23.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
and not the practices of Israel.”

00:04:25.748 --> 00:04:29.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
That sounds like a wonderful commendation,
doesn’t it?

00:04:29.352 --> 00:04:33.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, Jehoshaphat was a faithful king.

00:04:33.222 --> 00:04:37.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
He made the wise decision
to worship Jehovah.

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:39.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
But even so,

00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:43.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
he still made
some very unwise decisions.

00:04:44.334 --> 00:04:47.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read
about one of those unwise decisions

00:04:47.470 --> 00:04:51.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
at 2 Chronicles 18:1:

00:04:53.609 --> 00:04:58.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehoshaphat had riches
and glory in abundance,

00:04:58.147 --> 00:05:02.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
but he made a marriage alliance with Ahab.”

00:05:03.519 --> 00:05:08.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, he made his son
marry Ahab’s daughter Athaliah.

00:05:08.291 --> 00:05:10.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, that was a very unwise decision.

00:05:10.827 --> 00:05:12.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:05:12.829 --> 00:05:16.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because Ahab had built a temple for Baal

00:05:16.332 --> 00:05:21.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
and had even employed 850 false prophets.

00:05:21.304 --> 00:05:25.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ahab was also married
to wicked Queen Jezebel.

00:05:26.542 --> 00:05:31.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
Who would want their child
to marry into such a bad family?

00:05:31.047 --> 00:05:34.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
What was Jehoshaphat thinking?

00:05:34.217 --> 00:05:37.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why did he arrange for this marriage?

00:05:37.787 --> 00:05:41.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perhaps he wanted to reunite the 12 tribes,

00:05:41.157 --> 00:05:44.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
or he may have had some political
and commercial motives

00:05:44.427 --> 00:05:47.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
for wanting to have Ahab as an ally.

00:05:47.897 --> 00:05:50.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even though we don’t know
for sure the reason,

00:05:50.967 --> 00:05:55.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
we do know there were consequences.

00:05:55.505 --> 00:05:58.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because of this close relationship with Ahab,

00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:02.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat felt obligated to support Ahab

00:06:02.278 --> 00:06:05.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a war against the Syrians.

00:06:05.114 --> 00:06:09.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, this led
to yet another unwise decision.

00:06:10.853 --> 00:06:13.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
As they were preparing for this battle,

00:06:13.589 --> 00:06:18.261 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat asked for direction
from one of Jehovah’s prophets.

00:06:18.261 --> 00:06:22.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ahab, though, expressed
his hatred for the prophet

00:06:22.165 --> 00:06:24.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
and, after hearing the prophet’s message,

00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:27.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
had him thrown into prison.

00:06:27.336 --> 00:06:32.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
At that point,
it was decision time for Jehoshaphat.

00:06:33.209 --> 00:06:36.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did he decide to do?

00:06:36.112 --> 00:06:39.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
Although he initially disagreed with Ahab,

00:06:39.282 --> 00:06:42.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
he eventually joined him in the battle.

00:06:42.785 --> 00:06:46.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat disregarded
the warning from Jehovah.

00:06:46.789 --> 00:06:51.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
But then this led him
to still another unwise decision

00:06:51.694 --> 00:06:55.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
—this time an incredibly foolish decision.

00:06:55.865 --> 00:06:57.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
What happened?

00:06:57.934 --> 00:07:00.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s prophet had foretold

00:07:00.303 --> 00:07:04.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the Israelites would lose
their shepherd, or king, in battle.

00:07:04.707 --> 00:07:08.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Ahab said that he would disguise himself

00:07:08.377 --> 00:07:12.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
and not enter the battle dressed as a king.

00:07:12.415 --> 00:07:17.019 line:90% position:50% align:center
He then said that Jehoshaphat
should still dress like a king.

00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:20.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, just think about that for a moment.

00:07:20.723 --> 00:07:23.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ahab was basically saying,

00:07:23.426 --> 00:07:27.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You go out into battle
with a target on your back,

00:07:27.096 --> 00:07:29.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I’ll hide in disguise.’

00:07:29.198 --> 00:07:31.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
Really?

00:07:31.234 --> 00:07:34.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat’s decision to agree to do that

00:07:34.303 --> 00:07:37.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
was not only unwise but also foolish.

00:07:37.773 --> 00:07:40.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
It nearly cost him his life.

00:07:40.443 --> 00:07:42.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
So why would he do that? 

00:07:43.513 --> 00:07:45.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Insight on the Scriptures</i>  says

00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:48.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
that perhaps Jehoshaphat
didn’t want “to go back

00:07:48.651 --> 00:07:52.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
on his original promise to accompany Ahab.”

00:07:52.421 --> 00:07:54.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
So maybe he would have lost face

00:07:54.624 --> 00:07:57.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
if he backed out
of the agreement at that point.

00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:01.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
Although Jehoshaphat did survive the battle,

00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:04.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah sent another prophet to him

00:08:04.100 --> 00:08:08.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
to say what’s recorded at 2 Chronicles 19:2:

00:08:10.072 --> 00:08:13.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Is it the wicked you should be helping,

00:08:13.042 --> 00:08:17.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and is it those
who hate Jehovah you should love?

00:08:17.146 --> 00:08:21.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because of this the indignation
of Jehovah is against you.”

00:08:23.119 --> 00:08:25.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
Although Jehovah acknowledged

00:08:25.288 --> 00:08:27.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
the good things
that Jehoshaphat had accomplished

00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:30.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
in other aspects of his life,

00:08:30.526 --> 00:08:34.497 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat clearly made
some very unwise decisions.

00:08:35.531 --> 00:08:39.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
What lessons do we learn
from Jehoshaphat’s wrong decisions?

00:08:39.969 --> 00:08:41.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lesson 1:

00:08:41.871 --> 00:08:46.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just because we’ve done
many good things in Jehovah’s service

00:08:46.008 --> 00:08:50.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
doesn’t mean
that we’ll always make wise decisions.

00:08:50.479 --> 00:08:52.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lesson 2:

00:08:52.481 --> 00:08:55.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
Making friendships with those
who hate Jehovah

00:08:55.718 --> 00:09:00.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
can put us under pressure
to make other unwise decisions.

00:09:01.157 --> 00:09:03.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lesson 3:

00:09:03.259 --> 00:09:06.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even though
we may seek Jehovah’s direction,

00:09:06.562 --> 00:09:10.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
we must follow it
if we want to make wise decisions.

00:09:11.601 --> 00:09:13.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lesson 4:

00:09:13.603 --> 00:09:17.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we realize
that we’ve made an unwise decision,

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:20.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t keep going in the same course.

00:09:20.076 --> 00:09:22.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stop and change direction.

00:09:24.280 --> 00:09:26.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
These lessons can be summarized

00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:29.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the words of Proverbs 22:3.

00:09:29.452 --> 00:09:31.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
There we’re told:

00:09:31.454 --> 00:09:36.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The shrewd one sees the danger
and conceals himself,

00:09:36.459 --> 00:09:39.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but the inexperienced keep right on going

00:09:39.962 --> 00:09:42.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and suffer the consequences.”

00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:48.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, we need to see
the possible consequences of wrong decisions

00:09:48.337 --> 00:09:50.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then take action to avoid them.

00:09:51.907 --> 00:09:53.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
What were some of the consequences

00:09:53.943 --> 00:09:56.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehoshaphat’s unwise decisions?

00:09:57.380 --> 00:10:00.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
It nearly cost him his life.

00:10:00.182 --> 00:10:03.152 line:90% position:50% align:center
His oldest son died an apostate.

00:10:03.152 --> 00:10:06.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
And later, his daughter-in-law Athaliah

00:10:06.222 --> 00:10:09.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
killed all the heirs to the throne
except one baby

00:10:09.959 --> 00:10:13.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
and set herself up as queen of Judah.

00:10:14.597 --> 00:10:17.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
But you might be thinking,

00:10:17.033 --> 00:10:20.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Still, Jehovah viewed Jehoshaphat
as a good king.’

00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:22.471 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, he did.

00:10:22.471 --> 00:10:24.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s encouraging for us to know

00:10:24.674 --> 00:10:28.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
that even if we have made
some unwise decisions,

00:10:28.311 --> 00:10:33.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s possible that Jehovah
may still view us as his faithful servants.

00:10:34.350 --> 00:10:39.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does that mean, then,
that our decisions are not so important? 

00:10:40.456 --> 00:10:42.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>The Watchtower </i> back in 1980

00:10:42.992 --> 00:10:45.761 line:90% position:50% align:center
made this interesting comparison.

00:10:45.761 --> 00:10:49.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
It used an illustration of two ship captains.

00:10:49.432 --> 00:10:53.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
One skillfully maneuvered his ship
through a storm,

00:10:53.202 --> 00:10:57.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
bringing the vessel
and his crew safely to shore.

00:10:57.039 --> 00:11:01.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the other captain made unwise decisions,

00:11:01.110 --> 00:11:06.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
and because of that,
he experienced shipwreck

00:11:06.048 --> 00:11:08.250 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the same storm, saving only his life.

00:11:08.984 --> 00:11:12.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
While both captains escaped with their lives,

00:11:12.855 --> 00:11:15.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
the one whose ship remained intact

00:11:15.257 --> 00:11:19.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
would certainly enjoy
greater happiness and honor, wouldn’t he?

00:11:20.830 --> 00:11:23.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s obvious
which captain Jehoshaphat was like.

00:11:24.834 --> 00:11:26.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
Unlike Jehoshaphat,

00:11:26.869 --> 00:11:31.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
surely we’d prefer
to be like the successful captain

00:11:31.073 --> 00:11:33.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the one whose ship remained intact.

00:11:35.010 --> 00:11:39.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
How can we make sure
that we are like the successful captain?

00:11:40.082 --> 00:11:44.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
Back in 2011, the April <i>Watchtower</i>

00:11:44.453 --> 00:11:49.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
had a special chart
entitled “Steps to Making Good Decisions.”

00:11:50.259 --> 00:11:54.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
It listed these steps
in making wise decisions:

00:11:55.931 --> 00:12:00.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) Avoid being presumptuous.

00:12:00.302 --> 00:12:03.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) Do research.

00:12:03.572 --> 00:12:06.776 line:90% position:50% align:center
(3) Pray for wisdom.

00:12:06.776 --> 00:12:09.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
(4) Make the decision.

00:12:09.779 --> 00:12:12.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
(5) Implement the decision.

00:12:12.314 --> 00:12:14.884 line:90% position:50% align:center
But then there was an additional step:

00:12:14.884 --> 00:12:18.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
(6) Review and adjust.

00:12:19.622 --> 00:12:22.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is step 6 listed?

00:12:22.057 --> 00:12:24.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, from time to time,

00:12:24.393 --> 00:12:28.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
we need to review decisions
we’ve already made.

00:12:28.664 --> 00:12:32.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we do so, perhaps we’ll come to realize

00:12:32.067 --> 00:12:35.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
that some of them
were not the best decisions.

00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:39.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you still be like the successful captain?

00:12:39.642 --> 00:12:41.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, you can!

00:12:41.143 --> 00:12:42.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
How?

00:12:42.311 --> 00:12:45.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you courageously make
the needed adjustments.

00:12:47.049 --> 00:12:49.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
We must acknowledge that not all decisions

00:12:49.819 --> 00:12:52.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
work out exactly as we had planned.

00:12:52.822 --> 00:12:56.091 line:90% position:50% align:center
As Ecclesiastes 9:11 reminds us,

00:12:56.091 --> 00:13:00.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
“time and unexpected events
overtake [us] all.”

00:13:01.063 --> 00:13:04.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what should we do if that’s the case?

00:13:04.867 --> 00:13:07.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
The same <i>Watchtower </i> of 2011

00:13:07.870 --> 00:13:10.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
answers that question for us.

00:13:10.506 --> 00:13:14.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
After saying that Jehovah expects us
to live up to such decisions

00:13:14.944 --> 00:13:18.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
as our dedication and our marriage vows,

00:13:18.547 --> 00:13:20.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
it went on to say:

00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:24.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Most decisions, though, are less weighty.

00:13:24.587 --> 00:13:27.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
“A wise person will from time to time

00:13:27.857 --> 00:13:31.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
“review the decisions he has made.

00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:33.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will not let pride or stubbornness

00:13:33.662 --> 00:13:35.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
“prevent him from adjusting

00:13:35.664 --> 00:13:38.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
“or even reversing a decision.

00:13:38.234 --> 00:13:41.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
“His prime concern is to make sure

00:13:41.136 --> 00:13:44.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
that his life course continues to honor God.”

00:13:46.041 --> 00:13:49.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thinking back
to the illustration of the two captains,

00:13:49.845 --> 00:13:54.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
at times they may need
to reverse a former unwise decision.

00:13:55.451 --> 00:14:00.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
That happened
during a hurricane back in 1889.

00:14:01.557 --> 00:14:04.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
The captain of the British ship <i>Calliope</i>

00:14:04.860 --> 00:14:09.832 line:90% position:50% align:center
was anchored in the harbor
in Apia, Western Samoa,

00:14:09.832 --> 00:14:12.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
when a hurricane started blowing.

00:14:12.868 --> 00:14:16.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
Initially, he decided,
like all the other captains in the harbor,

00:14:16.672 --> 00:14:19.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
to weather the storm where he was.

00:14:19.575 --> 00:14:24.113 line:90% position:50% align:center
But as the waves grew in height
and the dangers increased,

00:14:24.113 --> 00:14:27.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
the captain realized
he had made the wrong decision.

00:14:27.650 --> 00:14:30.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did he do?

00:14:30.286 --> 00:14:33.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
He courageously reversed his decision

00:14:33.756 --> 00:14:36.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
and headed out to open sea.

00:14:36.492 --> 00:14:39.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was difficult, but ultimately 

00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.730 line:90% position:50% align:center
he saved himself,

00:14:41.730 --> 00:14:46.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
his ship, and the 250 sailors on board.

00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:51.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
This bold act of courage
entered him into the annals of naval history.

00:14:52.942 --> 00:14:55.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
To be like that courageous captain,

00:14:55.377 --> 00:15:00.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
at times we need
to prayerfully reexamine our past decisions.

00:15:00.849 --> 00:15:04.019 line:90% position:50% align:center
These could be decisions
about our employment,

00:15:04.019 --> 00:15:07.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
entertainment, education,
or even where we live.

00:15:08.791 --> 00:15:11.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we made the original decisions,

00:15:11.594 --> 00:15:14.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
they may have seemed wise to us.

00:15:14.463 --> 00:15:17.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do they still seem that way now?

00:15:18.467 --> 00:15:22.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we see the dangerous winds
of bad consequences

00:15:22.304 --> 00:15:25.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the frightening
waves of disaster approaching

00:15:25.441 --> 00:15:29.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
because our decisions were not
completely in harmony with Jehovah’s will,

00:15:29.878 --> 00:15:31.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
what should we do?

00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:34.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be like the wise captain.

00:15:34.383 --> 00:15:36.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t worry about losing face.

00:15:36.518 --> 00:15:38.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be courageous!

00:15:38.520 --> 00:15:42.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
Pray for Jehovah’s help,
and then take bold action.

00:15:42.524 --> 00:15:44.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
Make the changes you need to make

00:15:44.727 --> 00:15:47.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order to continue to please Jehovah.

00:15:47.830 --> 00:15:51.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this way, you’ll make the wise decision

00:15:51.667 --> 00:15:53.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the one that leads to success,

00:15:53.936 --> 00:15:56.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
the one that Jehovah will bless.

00:15:58.707 --> 00:16:02.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
One thing that will help us
make wise decisions 

00:16:02.611 --> 00:16:05.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
is to remember the big picture,

00:16:05.147 --> 00:16:07.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just what happens today,

00:16:07.716 --> 00:16:10.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
but how this will affect our future.

00:16:10.719 --> 00:16:15.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
In other words, don’t just think of now

00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:17.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
—think of forever.

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:21.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s the theme of our music video
for this month.

00:16:29.138 --> 00:16:36.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this world, it can be hard—
Not just to follow your heart—

00:16:36.679 --> 00:16:45.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
To be diff’rent
and do what’s right.

00:16:45.354 --> 00:16:53.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jehovah tells us in his Word:
‘Don’t be molded by this world.’

00:16:53.662 --> 00:17:00.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
He promises life
in Paradise.

00:17:00.235 --> 00:17:08.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
So stand tall;
give your all.

00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:16.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s right there with you;
he won’t let you fall.

00:17:16.185 --> 00:17:23.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
And pray
ev’ry day

00:17:23.959 --> 00:17:31.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
To climb those mountains out there
standing in your way.

00:17:31.033 --> 00:17:43.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, don’t live for today;
live for forever.

00:17:47.583 --> 00:17:54.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
They will try and offer fame—
Put a spotlight on your name,

00:17:54.890 --> 00:18:02.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
