00:20:09.091 --> 00:20:12.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
No matter how long
we’ve been serving Jehovah

00:20:12.227 --> 00:20:14.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
or what changes we face in life,

00:20:14.529 --> 00:20:18.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can always
keep our hope of living forever.

00:20:18.267 --> 00:20:20.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
Reflecting on this hope

00:20:20.269 --> 00:20:24.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
can help us make wise decisions
at any stage in life.

00:20:25.641 --> 00:20:28.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
Earlier we discussed that, at times,

00:20:28.477 --> 00:20:32.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
we need to review
a decision we made previously.

00:20:32.047 --> 00:20:34.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
In our next segment,

00:20:34.049 --> 00:20:38.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
a family decides to move
to a foreign-language field.

00:20:38.487 --> 00:20:42.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does this prove
to be a wise decision for them?

00:20:42.024 --> 00:20:44.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see how things turn out.

00:20:57.072 --> 00:20:58.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, you.

00:20:58.106 --> 00:20:59.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
Are you ready?

00:21:15.991 --> 00:21:19.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Haitian community in our area
was growing,

00:21:21.263 --> 00:21:25.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
and a new Haitian Creole congregation
was formed nearby.

00:21:26.601 --> 00:21:28.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
We checked out their territory

00:21:28.603 --> 00:21:30.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
and saw that they needed a lot of help.

00:21:32.307 --> 00:21:34.343 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Step on over.”

00:21:36.011 --> 00:21:37.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
So should we do this?

00:21:37.646 --> 00:21:39.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve been praying for more studies.

00:21:39.982 --> 00:21:41.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think this might just be my answer.

00:21:41.984 --> 00:21:42.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:43.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m in.

00:21:43.185 --> 00:21:45.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
Good. Then as soon as we get home,
we can pray about it.

00:21:49.458 --> 00:21:52.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our new language was exciting.

00:21:53.762 --> 00:21:56.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
We spent every spare second we had

00:21:56.365 --> 00:21:57.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
trying to get better.

00:22:02.304 --> 00:22:04.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had so much joy,

00:22:04.940 --> 00:22:06.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we had challenges too.

00:22:30.899 --> 00:22:31.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nicolas,

00:22:32.868 --> 00:22:34.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nicolas,

00:22:36.171 --> 00:22:38.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
could you read the next paragraph
for us, please?

00:22:40.108 --> 00:22:42.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, sorry.
Where are we?

00:22:51.686 --> 00:22:55.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our study was so nice today,
wasn’t it, Nicolas?

00:22:55.791 --> 00:22:57.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was.

00:22:57.392 --> 00:23:00.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet again, I was totally lost.

00:23:01.396 --> 00:23:04.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
We didn’t realize
that Nico just wasn’t finding

00:23:04.633 --> 00:23:06.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
the same joy as us.

00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:12.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
To help Nico,
we did a few more things in our language.

00:23:14.376 --> 00:23:16.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
Besides family worship,

00:23:16.411 --> 00:23:18.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
we attended one meeting a month

00:23:18.747 --> 00:23:20.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our old congregation.

00:23:21.450 --> 00:23:24.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, honestly,
I’m a little worried about Nico.

00:23:24.519 --> 00:23:27.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
He’s having a tough time
adapting to our new congregation.

00:23:27.622 --> 00:23:29.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm, I get it.

00:23:29.357 --> 00:23:32.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, back when we first joined
a foreign-language congregation,

00:23:32.861 --> 00:23:34.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
everything was fun and new.

00:23:34.863 --> 00:23:36.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
But after a little while,

00:23:36.665 --> 00:23:40.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
we noticed that our kids
had lost their enthusiasm.

00:23:40.035 --> 00:23:42.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were still hearing about Jehovah,

00:23:42.137 --> 00:23:45.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
but, honestly, they weren’t learning
because it wasn’t in their language.

00:23:45.974 --> 00:23:47.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is that why you moved back?

00:23:47.709 --> 00:23:48.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was.

00:23:48.877 --> 00:23:50.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
But every family is different.

00:23:50.479 --> 00:23:53.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
We each have to decide
what’s best for our own.

00:23:53.582 --> 00:23:55.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks, that’s true.

00:23:56.218 --> 00:23:58.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
I found the perfect article

00:23:58.854 --> 00:24:01.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
to help us decide what to do.

00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:03.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
It mentioned the example of Daniel.

00:24:04.326 --> 00:24:07.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
He had to speak
different languages every day,

00:24:07.629 --> 00:24:12.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
but he made sure to study in Hebrew,
his language.

00:24:14.369 --> 00:24:18.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
The article mentioned Psalm 119:11:

00:24:18.673 --> 00:24:22.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
“In my heart I treasure up your saying.”

00:24:23.745 --> 00:24:27.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
For Nico to treasure God’s Word in his heart,

00:24:27.516 --> 00:24:30.218 line:90% position:50% align:center
we felt he needed even more guidance

00:24:30.218 --> 00:24:32.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the language of his heart.

00:24:35.757 --> 00:24:37.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
The truth is,

00:24:37.192 --> 00:24:39.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
when I’m at the meeting in my language,
it’s different.

00:24:39.661 --> 00:24:42.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t have to think a lot
just to understand what I’m hearing.

00:24:42.430 --> 00:24:45.400 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, I think it’s clear
what’s best for our family.

00:24:45.400 --> 00:24:46.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is.

00:24:46.401 --> 00:24:48.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what about your students?

00:24:48.403 --> 00:24:51.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s OK, Nico.
We’ll find a way to help them.

00:24:51.206 --> 00:24:54.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
The language we’re immersed in every day
is the language of your heart.

00:24:54.709 --> 00:24:57.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
So it’s best for you
to keep growing spiritually

00:24:57.379 --> 00:24:59.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
in that same language.

00:25:01.249 --> 00:25:03.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was the best decision

00:25:03.585 --> 00:25:06.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order for Nico to stay close to Jehovah.

00:25:08.857 --> 00:25:12.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we did miss the Haitian Creole field.

00:25:12.394 --> 00:25:14.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
So a few years later . . .

00:25:15.564 --> 00:25:16.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
Are you ready?

00:25:16.765 --> 00:25:19.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m a little nervous, but I think I’m ready.

00:25:23.238 --> 00:25:25.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
We decided it was the right time

00:25:25.373 --> 00:25:27.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
to move back.

00:25:29.945 --> 00:25:33.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re so glad our decision helped Nico

00:25:33.248 --> 00:25:35.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
build a solid foundation

00:25:35.684 --> 00:25:39.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
for his faith and his future.

00:25:41.323 --> 00:25:44.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
How encouraging it was to be reminded

00:25:44.059 --> 00:25:46.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
that when we make a decision,

00:25:46.061 --> 00:25:49.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can always make adjustments later!

00:25:49.731 --> 00:25:54.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever made a decision
that seemed wise at first,

00:25:54.069 --> 00:25:58.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
but then over time,
as things changed in your life,

00:25:58.039 --> 00:26:00.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
didn’t seem so good?

00:26:00.508 --> 00:26:04.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe you felt, ‘I’ll be a failure
if I leave this assignment.’

00:26:05.814 --> 00:26:08.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, our primary concern

00:26:08.850 --> 00:26:13.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
must be to make sure
that our life course continues to honor God.

00:26:14.623 --> 00:26:17.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have the courage
to consider making a change

00:26:17.659 --> 00:26:20.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
if your circumstances have changed.

