00:26:41.683 --> 00:26:45.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
on your child’s love for Jehovah?

00:26:46.087 --> 00:26:48.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
What kind of a price tag can you put

00:26:48.189 --> 00:26:51.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
on serving Jehovah whole-souled as a family?

00:26:53.061 --> 00:26:55.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I found out
that we were going to have a family,

00:26:57.098 --> 00:26:59.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
it was overwhelming for me.

00:26:59.100 --> 00:27:01.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you come into the truth—

00:27:01.670 --> 00:27:04.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
We weren’t Witnesses when I was a child.

00:27:04.372 --> 00:27:09.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes you’re exposed to things
that leave you with baggage,

00:27:09.377 --> 00:27:11.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
leave you unsure of yourself.

00:27:11.680 --> 00:27:16.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
You need constant reassurance
that you’re going to be OK,

00:27:16.551 --> 00:27:20.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
that you can take care
of any situation that comes along.

00:27:21.022 --> 00:27:24.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
My dad—he gave me all I needed.

00:27:24.125 --> 00:27:26.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
He loved me so much.

00:27:26.127 --> 00:27:28.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
I would take my mother’s knitting yarn,

00:27:28.029 --> 00:27:31.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I would tie it to his door handle
after he went to sleep.

00:27:31.533 --> 00:27:33.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I would run it
across the hall to my bedroom

00:27:33.968 --> 00:27:35.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
and tie it to my big toe

00:27:35.970 --> 00:27:37.972 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that when he opened
his door in the morning,

00:27:37.972 --> 00:27:39.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
I would wake up 
and I could be with him.

00:27:39.674 --> 00:27:43.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
That love that I had for my dad

00:27:43.411 --> 00:27:46.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
—I wanted them to love Jehovah that much.

00:27:46.848 --> 00:27:51.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wanted a string tied
around their hearts right to Jehovah

00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:53.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that he was the one motivating them

00:27:53.888 --> 00:27:57.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he was the one
waking them up spiritually every day.

00:27:58.159 --> 00:28:01.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
I loved to teach the children things,

00:28:01.563 --> 00:28:04.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I would do it at any available moment.

00:28:04.499 --> 00:28:06.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then, of course,
at night, as a family

00:28:06.835 --> 00:28:09.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
(usually on our bed),
we would read our Bible together.

00:28:09.604 --> 00:28:14.609 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was the glue that kept us tied to Jehovah

00:28:14.609 --> 00:28:17.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
and kept us tied to each other.

00:28:17.846 --> 00:28:20.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Judges 7, Gideon said:

00:28:20.582 --> 00:28:23.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Watch me and do . . . what I do.”

00:28:23.618 --> 00:28:28.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I knew that if we wanted
the children to live the truth,

00:28:29.591 --> 00:28:32.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
we had to live it with them.

00:28:32.360 --> 00:28:34.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
It couldn’t be something
that we just taught them.

00:28:35.597 --> 00:28:40.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had to live our life of service
to Jehovah with them.

00:28:41.736 --> 00:28:46.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus said that obviously
we ‘can’t slave for two masters.’

00:28:46.708 --> 00:28:49.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I’ve tried to do that and, believe me,
it does not work.

00:28:51.045 --> 00:28:55.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
Like any father,
I wanted to have a home for my family.

00:28:55.917 --> 00:28:57.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
My profession was building houses,

00:28:58.720 --> 00:29:02.056 line:90% position:50% align:center
but that cost me my pioneering.

00:29:02.056 --> 00:29:04.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so I decided

00:29:04.559 --> 00:29:06.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had to quit building houses.

00:29:06.561 --> 00:29:07.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I did.

00:29:07.796 --> 00:29:10.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started to do remodel jobs.

00:29:10.165 --> 00:29:12.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we looked for a place
that we could afford

00:29:12.934 --> 00:29:15.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
that would sustain us
in the full-time service,

00:29:15.737 --> 00:29:18.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jehovah provided
exactly what we needed.

00:29:20.308 --> 00:29:23.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the highlights of raising the children

00:29:23.511 --> 00:29:27.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
was the annual visits
to unassigned territory.

00:29:27.182 --> 00:29:30.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
The success in the ministry was phenomenal.

00:29:30.585 --> 00:29:33.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we decided as a family

00:29:33.254 --> 00:29:36.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
to take on the challenge of learning Spanish.

00:29:36.424 --> 00:29:39.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had a large Spanish-speaking population

00:29:39.961 --> 00:29:43.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
in our territory
and in the surrounding territories,

00:29:43.164 --> 00:29:46.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
and there was no group
or congregation to help them.

00:29:47.535 --> 00:29:52.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we would go out
of the country to preach, we would often stay

00:29:52.540 --> 00:29:54.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
with family members of our Bible students

00:29:54.876 --> 00:29:57.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
or our brothers and sisters
in these countries,

00:29:57.512 --> 00:30:01.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
in some very humble surroundings,

00:30:01.015 --> 00:30:03.218 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we took advantage

00:30:03.218 --> 00:30:05.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the hospitality that they offered us

00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:09.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we wanted
to live the culture with them.

00:30:09.624 --> 00:30:14.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
It just opened our eyes to a world
that we never knew existed.

00:30:16.531 --> 00:30:21.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our family was able to progress

00:30:21.536 --> 00:30:24.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
and flourish spiritually

00:30:24.138 --> 00:30:28.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
because of a concentrated effort
by Joren and me.

00:30:28.009 --> 00:30:30.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
She’s been there
to fill in all of the cracks.

00:30:30.845 --> 00:30:35.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
He always made it so easy to love him,

00:30:36.351 --> 00:30:39.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
to love the children,
and to really focus on spiritual things.

00:30:40.421 --> 00:30:43.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we pray to Jehovah,

00:30:43.191 --> 00:30:47.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
thinking about our family
being able to serve him like this,

00:30:47.228 --> 00:30:49.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
we just say thank you.

00:30:49.564 --> 00:30:54.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just try in some way
to express how deeply we feel

00:30:54.569 --> 00:30:56.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
about this privilege that we have

00:30:56.571 --> 00:31:01.509 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be with Kaarsten and Kjersti
and Andrea and Dhimo.

00:31:01.509 --> 00:31:03.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t deserve

00:31:03.611 --> 00:31:06.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
any of these blessings from Jehovah,

00:31:06.180 --> 00:31:10.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
but somehow he’s blessed our efforts,

00:31:10.618 --> 00:31:13.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he’s given us an opportunity to smile

00:31:13.922 --> 00:31:17.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
and reflect on all of the things
that he’s done for us.

00:31:17.859 --> 00:31:20.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what can we do to repay Jehovah

00:31:20.562 --> 00:31:23.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
but just keep going, keep trying,

00:31:23.698 --> 00:31:27.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
and keep moving forward
until we’re on the other side?

00:31:30.038 --> 00:31:32.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, Brother and Sister Harris ,

00:31:32.040 --> 00:31:36.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
for sharing your experience
in such a heartfelt way.

00:31:36.377 --> 00:31:40.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
You decided to put spiritual things first
in your children’s lives

00:31:40.882 --> 00:31:44.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
and gave them the chance
to have a friendship with Jehovah.

00:31:46.321 --> 00:31:48.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
What happens to us in childhood

00:31:48.890 --> 00:31:51.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
can shape who we become as adults,

00:31:51.659 --> 00:31:55.063 line:90% position:50% align:center
for better or for worse.

00:31:55.063 --> 00:32:00.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we don’t like who we are now,
we can change,

00:32:00.068 --> 00:32:05.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we’ll see in the latest installment
of <i>Where Are They Now?</i>

00:32:14.983 --> 00:32:16.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hello, who is it?

00:32:16.351 --> 00:32:18.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, hi. How are you?

00:32:18.419 --> 00:32:20.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK, come on up.

00:32:20.021 --> 00:32:22.490 line:90% position:50% align:center
My name is Enrique Torres, Jr.

00:32:22.490 --> 00:32:26.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
I live on Staten Island, New York,

00:32:26.194 --> 00:32:29.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I have the privilege to serve
in the Mid-Island Congregation.

00:32:42.877 --> 00:32:47.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first 40 years of my life were mired

00:32:47.615 --> 00:32:51.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a lifestyle that was horrendous.

00:32:51.285 --> 00:32:53.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
A judge stated that I had

00:32:53.388 --> 00:32:56.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
a “propensity for criminality.”

00:32:58.626 --> 00:33:01.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
No doubt, he was describing a vicious person.

00:33:08.736 --> 00:33:12.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a youth, I was hanging around
with the wrong kind of people

00:33:12.740 --> 00:33:15.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
that led me into a life of crime

00:33:15.710 --> 00:33:17.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
and debauchery.

00:33:18.813 --> 00:33:21.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
This captain in our prison came up

00:33:21.983 --> 00:33:23.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
with a psychological plan

00:33:23.985 --> 00:33:28.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
to take the individuals
that had the potential for leadership

00:33:28.656 --> 00:33:31.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
and put them in isolation.

00:33:31.225 --> 00:33:33.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wound up to be among them.

00:33:34.562 --> 00:33:37.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you imagine, they were getting beat up?

00:33:39.567 --> 00:33:43.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was becoming too much for me
—the screams and so forth.

00:33:43.638 --> 00:33:46.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
I said, “If this continues,
I’m not going to survive here.”

00:33:51.612 --> 00:33:54.148 line:90% position:50% align:center
I did get in contact with my father

00:33:54.148 --> 00:33:56.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he told me:

00:33:56.184 --> 00:33:57.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Never forget Jehovah.

00:33:57.852 --> 00:34:01.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
That is his name.”

00:34:01.989 --> 00:34:04.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s all I got out of it.

00:34:04.592 --> 00:34:08.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
I knew that there was nobody
that could help me but God.

00:34:08.496 --> 00:34:12.467 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that’s when I found myself
in prayer to Jehovah.

00:34:13.668 --> 00:34:17.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
I vowed that I would make it my business
to learn more about him

00:34:17.038 --> 00:34:18.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
than just his name.

00:34:18.773 --> 00:34:20.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
At that time, that’s all I knew.

00:34:21.042 --> 00:34:25.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
I got some literature; I got the Bible too.

00:34:25.046 --> 00:34:28.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah became more meaningful to me.

00:34:28.449 --> 00:34:31.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s when he became real to me.

00:34:32.286 --> 00:34:35.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was the first 40 years of my life.

00:34:35.456 --> 00:34:38.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the last 40 years of my life

00:34:38.326 --> 00:34:41.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
with Jehovah’s training
from his organization,

00:34:41.829 --> 00:34:46.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
my personality—it was transformed.

00:34:46.534 --> 00:34:48.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
The blessings that I have received

00:34:48.569 --> 00:34:51.339 line:90% position:50% align:center
have been in the area of my field service

00:34:51.339 --> 00:34:54.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also my teaching ability,

00:34:54.208 --> 00:34:58.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
which has helped me
to be able to draw closer to Jehovah.

00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:04.385 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was privileged to become
a ministerial servant for many years

00:35:04.385 --> 00:35:07.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
and a field service overseer
for many more years.

00:35:09.991 --> 00:35:14.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the main challenges that I’m facing is

00:35:14.762 --> 00:35:18.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
that I have developed cancer

00:35:18.332 --> 00:35:22.170 line:90% position:50% align:center
and have gone through four cancer operations

00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:24.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also some chemotherapy.

00:35:24.539 --> 00:35:28.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
Without relying upon Jehovah to help me

00:35:28.109 --> 00:35:31.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
to overcome these challenges,

00:35:31.512 --> 00:35:35.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
there’s no doubt in my mind that I
never would have been able to make it.

00:35:38.085 --> 00:35:42.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
I would recommend to avoid
that trap that I fell into

00:35:42.190 --> 00:35:45.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
—hanging around with street gangs

00:35:45.426 --> 00:35:50.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then getting involved
in burglaries and robberies.

00:35:50.431 --> 00:35:52.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s a progression.

00:35:52.433 --> 00:35:56.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was not anything of value at all.

00:35:56.370 --> 00:36:00.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead, what it brought me
was a lot of grief,

00:36:00.741 --> 00:36:05.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
mental scars, and also
a lot of trouble with my conscience.

00:36:07.415 --> 00:36:10.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
Study God’s Word, the Bible,
so that you may be able

00:36:10.785 --> 00:36:15.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see what Jehovah has in store
for the future.

00:36:15.156 --> 00:36:19.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
And also, you’ll be able to see
that he’s a kind, merciful, loving God

00:36:19.927 --> 00:36:24.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
that doesn’t want anyone to be destroyed
but wants them to have life.

00:36:25.633 --> 00:36:29.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
Parents, never give up on your children.

00:36:29.070 --> 00:36:31.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah never gave up on me.

00:36:33.507 --> 00:36:38.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
He rescued me from this spiritual darkness
that I was in,

00:36:38.512 --> 00:36:42.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he brought me into his light

00:36:42.149 --> 00:36:45.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to his wonderful organization.

00:36:45.086 --> 00:36:49.123 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I give him all the credit for that.

00:36:49.123 --> 00:36:51.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when I speak to people,
that’s what I tell them.

00:36:51.525 --> 00:36:53.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
I tell them: “It wasn’t me.

00:36:53.794 --> 00:36:56.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It was Jehovah that has done all of this,

00:36:56.464 --> 00:37:00.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he could do that for you too
if you give him an opportunity.”

00:37:05.940 --> 00:37:09.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
Early in life,
Enrique’s poor choice of friends

00:37:09.744 --> 00:37:13.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
led him to make many other bad decisions.

00:37:13.514 --> 00:37:18.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in his 40’s,
he decided to get to know Jehovah.

00:37:18.185 --> 00:37:20.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a good reminder

00:37:20.187 --> 00:37:24.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we can continue
to make changes later on in life!

00:37:24.392 --> 00:37:27.995 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you parents, please keep in mind

00:37:27.995 --> 00:37:31.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the seeds of truth you planted
in your children’s hearts

00:37:31.465 --> 00:37:34.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
can move them to make good decisions later,

00:37:34.535 --> 00:37:36.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
even as adults.

00:37:37.972 --> 00:37:41.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of our decisions may seem small,

00:37:41.442 --> 00:37:45.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
yet they can have a powerful effect
on our brotherhood.

00:37:45.947 --> 00:37:49.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the next video,
Brother Robert Luccioni

00:37:49.183 --> 00:37:52.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
discusses how our response to someone

00:37:52.420 --> 00:37:55.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
can make peace or break it.

00:37:57.291 --> 00:37:59.327 line:10% position:50% align:center
So our Scripture text for today

00:37:59.327 --> 00:38:01.662 line:10% position:50% align:center
discusses the qualities needed

00:38:01.662 --> 00:38:03.698 line:10% position:50% align:center
“to walk worthily”

00:38:03.698 --> 00:38:05.833 line:10% position:50% align:center
and in a way that pleases Jehovah.

00:38:05.833 --> 00:38:09.270 line:10% position:50% align:center
Now, you notice our Scripture text,

00:38:09.270 --> 00:38:12.406 line:10% position:50% align:center
Ephesians 4:1, is only a partial sentence.

00:38:12.406 --> 00:38:16.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read the entire sentence,
which takes in verses 1-3.

00:38:16.510 --> 00:38:20.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ephesians 4:1-3—he says:

00:38:20.514 --> 00:38:22.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Therefore I, the prisoner in the Lord,

00:38:22.450 --> 00:38:26.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
“appeal to you to walk worthily
of the calling with which you were called,

00:38:26.120 --> 00:38:30.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
“with all humility
and mildness, with patience,

00:38:30.558 --> 00:38:32.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
“putting up with one another in love,

00:38:32.760 --> 00:38:36.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
“earnestly endeavoring
to maintain the oneness of the spirit

00:38:36.797 --> 00:38:39.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the uniting bond of peace.”

00:38:39.934 --> 00:38:44.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
So here the apostle Paul
links ‘walking worthily’ with unity,

00:38:44.939 --> 00:38:47.808 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you notice the qualities
that are needed to do that.

00:38:47.808 --> 00:38:52.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
He says that we need ‘humility,
mildness, and patience.’

00:38:52.380 --> 00:38:55.216 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, this is not the only time
that the apostle Paul

00:38:55.216 --> 00:38:57.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
links these three qualities
with being in unity.

00:38:57.885 --> 00:39:01.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may remember Colossians 3:12,

00:39:01.222 --> 00:39:03.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it tells us
to “clothe [ourselves] with . . .

00:39:03.591 --> 00:39:06.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
humility, mildness, and patience.”

00:39:06.193 --> 00:39:07.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:39:07.161 --> 00:39:10.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that we can
“continue putting up with one another.”

00:39:10.331 --> 00:39:14.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
So why are these qualities
so essential to peace and to unity?

00:39:14.502 --> 00:39:16.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what do the Scriptures say about them?

00:39:16.570 --> 00:39:18.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, perhaps we think of the scripture

00:39:18.506 --> 00:39:21.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Philippians 2:3, 4, which says:

00:39:21.409 --> 00:39:24.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do nothing out of contentiousness
or out of egotism,

00:39:24.245 --> 00:39:27.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
but with humility
consider others superior to you.”

00:39:27.415 --> 00:39:29.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, that brings about peace and unity.

00:39:29.483 --> 00:39:32.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or Proverbs 15:1:

00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:36.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
“A mild answer turns away rage.”

00:39:36.257 --> 00:39:38.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or Proverbs 25:15:

00:39:38.959 --> 00:39:42.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
“By patience a commander is won over.”

00:39:42.696 --> 00:39:46.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, humility, mildness, patience

00:39:46.167 --> 00:39:48.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
—these qualities are so vital

00:39:48.402 --> 00:39:51.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
for taking tension out of a situation

00:39:51.806 --> 00:39:56.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
and allowing for humility
and unity and peace.

00:39:56.377 --> 00:39:59.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, there are many accounts in the Bible
that illustrate this fact,

00:39:59.213 --> 00:40:01.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re going to consider just one

00:40:01.082 --> 00:40:04.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that of the Ephraimites and Gideon.

00:40:04.351 --> 00:40:07.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you look in your Bibles
in Judges chapters 6 and 7,

00:40:07.154 --> 00:40:11.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
it sets out the account
of Gideon going against the Midianites.

00:40:11.659 --> 00:40:14.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
We remember that
in response to Jehovah’s direction,

00:40:14.328 --> 00:40:16.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gideon won against Midian

00:40:16.564 --> 00:40:18.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
—first with 32,000 men

00:40:18.566 --> 00:40:21.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then finally weeded down
to only 300 men.

00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:25.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, if you look in your Bibles,
the <i>Study Bible</i>  map B6 

00:40:25.739 --> 00:40:28.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
helps us to visualize the strategy

00:40:28.642 --> 00:40:31.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Gideon used with Jehovah’s direction.

00:40:31.345 --> 00:40:33.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, the Midianites

00:40:33.114 --> 00:40:35.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
gathered near the hill of Moreh,

00:40:35.583 --> 00:40:38.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you can see that here on the map.

00:40:38.319 --> 00:40:41.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you look at Judges 6:34,

00:40:41.622 --> 00:40:42.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re reminded

00:40:42.723 --> 00:40:45.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
that “Jehovah’s spirit came upon Gideon.”

00:40:45.759 --> 00:40:48.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
So here he’s operating
under Jehovah’s spirit.

00:40:48.395 --> 00:40:49.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what did he do?

00:40:49.663 --> 00:40:52.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
First off, he calls
on the tribes of Manasseh,

00:40:52.466 --> 00:40:55.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali to assist.

00:40:55.636 --> 00:40:56.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that makes sense

00:40:56.570 --> 00:40:58.339 line:90% position:50% align:center
because you can see where those tribes were

00:40:58.339 --> 00:41:01.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
in relation to where the fighting was going to be.

00:41:01.308 --> 00:41:03.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then at Judges 7:22,

00:41:03.944 --> 00:41:05.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gideon’s initial attack

00:41:05.946 --> 00:41:07.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
threw the Midianites into confusion.

00:41:07.982 --> 00:41:09.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so the Midianites

00:41:09.316 --> 00:41:12.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
fled south toward Abel-meholah.

00:41:12.453 --> 00:41:14.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 23 of chapter 7 says

00:41:14.688 --> 00:41:16.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he then calls on Naphtali,

00:41:16.724 --> 00:41:18.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
Asher, and Manasseh

00:41:18.459 --> 00:41:20.728 line:90% position:50% align:center
to chase after them and push them

00:41:20.728 --> 00:41:22.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
toward the south, further south.

00:41:22.696 --> 00:41:25.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you can see the logic in that.

00:41:25.266 --> 00:41:28.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
But then in an excellent strategy

00:41:28.269 --> 00:41:30.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
in verses 24 and 25, to head them off,

00:41:30.905 --> 00:41:33.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
he also calls on Ephraim

00:41:33.007 --> 00:41:35.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
to capture the waters as far as Beth-barah

00:41:35.843 --> 00:41:37.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
and block their escape, and they do.

00:41:37.978 --> 00:41:39.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they’re successful;

00:41:39.680 --> 00:41:42.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
the two main princes of Midian are killed.

00:41:42.616 --> 00:41:45.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s victory
—an excellent strategy—

00:41:45.419 --> 00:41:48.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
one of the greatest and most courageous

00:41:48.189 --> 00:41:49.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
and bravest battles in the Bible.

00:41:49.757 --> 00:41:51.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, interestingly,

00:41:51.125 --> 00:41:53.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
there’s no record ever again

00:41:53.394 --> 00:41:55.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Midianites bothering Jehovah’s people

00:41:55.896 --> 00:41:57.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
after this victory.

00:41:57.765 --> 00:42:00.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you imagine having a share in that project,

00:42:00.634 --> 00:42:02.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
how excited you would be?

00:42:02.803 --> 00:42:04.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, not everybody was.

00:42:04.772 --> 00:42:07.541 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look at Judges 8:1;

00:42:08.609 --> 00:42:12.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
it says: “Then the men of Ephraim
said to him [to Gideon]:

00:42:12.413 --> 00:42:14.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘What have you done to us?

00:42:14.415 --> 00:42:17.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Why did you not call us
when you went to fight against Midian?’

00:42:17.051 --> 00:42:20.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they quarreled bitterly with him.”

00:42:20.788 --> 00:42:22.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
What was Ephraim’s problem?

00:42:22.790 --> 00:42:25.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, they felt they
should have been involved earlier

00:42:25.759 --> 00:42:28.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
or that perhaps the situation
should have been handled differently.

00:42:28.662 --> 00:42:30.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Why weren’t we involved?
Why didn’t you call us?

00:42:30.864 --> 00:42:32.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘We didn’t know anything that was going on.

00:42:32.666 --> 00:42:35.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then we had to drop everything
and come and bail you out.’

00:42:36.003 --> 00:42:40.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, did Ephraim
have humility, mildness, and patience?

00:42:40.407 --> 00:42:42.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, far from it.

00:42:42.209 --> 00:42:44.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it was disrupting unity.

00:42:44.645 --> 00:42:46.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, how did Gideon respond?

00:42:46.647 --> 00:42:49.183 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we remember,
Gideon had Jehovah’s spirit

00:42:49.183 --> 00:42:51.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he had an excellent strategy

00:42:51.252 --> 00:42:53.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
that led to an outstanding victory
for Jehovah.

00:42:53.587 --> 00:42:55.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did he respond?

00:42:55.322 --> 00:42:57.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, look at verses 2 and 3.

00:42:57.491 --> 00:43:02.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
It says: “But he said to them:
‘What have I done compared with you?

00:43:02.496 --> 00:43:07.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Are not the gleanings of Ephraim
better than the grape harvest of Abiezer?

00:43:07.234 --> 00:43:09.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘It was into your hand

00:43:09.236 --> 00:43:13.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘that God gave Midian’s princes
Oreb and Zeeb,

00:43:13.073 --> 00:43:15.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and what have I done compared with you?’

00:43:15.909 --> 00:43:19.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
When he spoke this way, they calmed down.”

00:43:19.313 --> 00:43:22.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, Gideon showed humility,

00:43:22.149 --> 00:43:24.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
mildness, and patience.

00:43:24.084 --> 00:43:24.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
The result?

00:43:24.985 --> 00:43:26.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everyone calmed down,

00:43:26.520 --> 00:43:30.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Gideon was able
to get on with Jehovah’s work at hand.

00:43:30.524 --> 00:43:35.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we contrast that to the next time
that the Ephraimites pulled the same trick,

00:43:35.262 --> 00:43:37.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
as recorded in Judges chapter 12.

00:43:37.498 --> 00:43:40.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
There you remember
that they accused Jephthah

00:43:40.100 --> 00:43:43.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
of not calling them into battle—same story.

00:43:43.037 --> 00:43:44.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did Jephthah do?

00:43:44.605 --> 00:43:46.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, he says:
‘Well, I did call you into battle,

00:43:46.173 --> 00:43:48.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you didn’t come,
so I just did it myself.’

00:43:48.042 --> 00:43:50.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
The next thing you know,
they’re fighting among themselves,

00:43:50.077 --> 00:43:54.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
completely distracted
from carrying on Jehovah’s work.

00:43:54.281 --> 00:43:56.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s the lesson?

00:43:56.317 --> 00:43:59.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the lesson is
that things happen at times

00:43:59.286 --> 00:44:02.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
that make peace go away.

00:44:02.389 --> 00:44:04.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes brothers in the congregation,

00:44:04.725 --> 00:44:07.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Bethel, on a construction site

00:44:07.161 --> 00:44:10.497 line:90% position:50% align:center
may react like Ephraimites.

00:44:10.497 --> 00:44:13.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes we react like Ephraimites.

00:44:13.634 --> 00:44:15.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Why didn’t you ask my opinion?

00:44:15.636 --> 00:44:17.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I was supposed to be involved in this.

00:44:17.638 --> 00:44:20.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Why did you call me last minute when
you knew you needed this two weeks ago,

00:44:20.774 --> 00:44:23.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
and now I have to drop everything
and help you out.’

00:44:23.377 --> 00:44:26.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, that happens; we’re only human.

00:44:26.213 --> 00:44:30.384 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, when it happens, how will we react?

00:44:30.384 --> 00:44:34.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, unity is more important
than who is right and who is wrong,

00:44:34.688 --> 00:44:37.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Gideon understood that simple truth.

00:44:37.991 --> 00:44:41.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
And unity is so important today.

00:44:41.795 --> 00:44:44.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
There was an interesting,
beautiful <i>Watchtower</i>  article

00:44:44.365 --> 00:44:48.369 line:90% position:50% align:center
in 2014, December 15,
and the article was entitled

00:44:48.369 --> 00:44:50.838 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Facing the End of This Old World Together.”

00:44:50.838 --> 00:44:53.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it stated this; it said:

00:44:53.474 --> 00:44:57.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
“One of the darkest periods
in human history nears. . . .

00:44:57.745 --> 00:45:02.216 line:90% position:50% align:center
For God’s people,
it will be a time for unity.”

00:45:02.216 --> 00:45:03.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
It goes on to say:

00:45:03.350 --> 00:45:06.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
“During the coming
time of trouble for this system,

00:45:06.053 --> 00:45:09.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will have to be truly united.”

00:45:09.923 --> 00:45:11.625 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let me ask you,

00:45:11.625 --> 00:45:13.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you think it’s any coincidence

00:45:13.927 --> 00:45:15.929 line:90% position:50% align:center
that here,
where we are in the stream of time,

00:45:15.929 --> 00:45:19.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we see Jehovah pulling his organization

00:45:19.299 --> 00:45:21.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
closer and closer together in unity?

00:45:21.535 --> 00:45:25.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is it any coincidence
that we hear over and over again

00:45:25.139 --> 00:45:27.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the need for peace and for unity?

00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:28.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
No!

00:45:28.409 --> 00:45:30.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, as this world
gets more and more divided,

00:45:30.878 --> 00:45:33.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
fragmented, fighting,

00:45:33.313 --> 00:45:36.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
we need to pull
tighter and tighter together in unity.

00:45:36.850 --> 00:45:38.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that requires that all of us

00:45:38.852 --> 00:45:40.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
work on these beautiful qualities

00:45:40.854 --> 00:45:44.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
of humility, mildness, and patience.

00:45:44.391 --> 00:45:46.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when there’s a lack of unity,
what do we have to do?

00:45:46.894 --> 00:45:48.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we have to look at ourselves.

00:45:48.629 --> 00:45:51.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, generally we find

00:45:51.131 --> 00:45:54.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the problem is me; it’s us.

00:45:54.735 --> 00:45:58.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe we weren’t consulted
as soon as we should have been.

00:45:58.772 --> 00:46:02.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or maybe our idea of how the work
or this thing should be done

00:46:02.976 --> 00:46:04.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
wasn’t shared by others.

00:46:04.978 --> 00:46:08.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in the grand scheme of things,
does it really make a difference?

00:46:08.882 --> 00:46:11.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
And many times
when we look at a situation afterward

00:46:11.185 --> 00:46:13.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we pull back unemotionally,

00:46:13.187 --> 00:46:17.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
we generally find that, well,
maybe our idea was pretty good,

00:46:17.524 --> 00:46:19.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
but the timing wasn’t good.

00:46:19.827 --> 00:46:22.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or maybe it wasn’t
that great of an idea after all.

00:46:22.696 --> 00:46:26.767 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or maybe there was more than one way
for this thing to be handled.

00:46:26.767 --> 00:46:29.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or perhaps Jehovah’s spirit

00:46:29.570 --> 00:46:32.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
was leading things in a different direction.

00:46:32.873 --> 00:46:37.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, again, what can help us
to not be an obstacle to unity?

00:46:37.110 --> 00:46:39.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
Humility, mildness, patience

00:46:39.246 --> 00:46:42.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
—just what we were considering
in Ephesians chapter 4.

00:46:42.583 --> 00:46:44.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, we have to have the confidence

00:46:44.618 --> 00:46:48.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
that if it’s important to Jehovah,
it’ll happen.

00:46:48.388 --> 00:46:50.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if not, what a shame it would be

00:46:50.591 --> 00:46:53.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we become an obstacle to unity

00:46:53.293 --> 00:46:57.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
over something
that’s not that important to Jehovah!

00:46:57.164 --> 00:47:01.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, brothers and sisters,
we need the “Gideons”

00:47:01.301 --> 00:47:04.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
to help us
in our support of the Governing Body.

00:47:04.771 --> 00:47:06.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gideon was such a beautiful example.

00:47:06.773 --> 00:47:09.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
Once he understood Jehovah’s direction,

00:47:09.476 --> 00:47:14.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
he was willing to run into the fire
for Jehovah and for his organization.

00:47:14.081 --> 00:47:16.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s what we need.
We need “Gideons.”

00:47:16.617 --> 00:47:19.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t need any more “Ephraimites.”

00:47:19.453 --> 00:47:21.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in harmony with today’s text,

00:47:21.855 --> 00:47:25.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
may each one of us walk worthily
in these last days

00:47:25.592 --> 00:47:29.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
and work on the qualities
of humility, mildness, and patience.

00:47:29.930 --> 00:47:34.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if we do,
we will be a uniting force for good

00:47:34.334 --> 00:47:38.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
and of Gideonlike value
to Jehovah and the organization

00:47:38.572 --> 00:47:40.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the troublesome days ahead.

00:47:41.975 --> 00:47:46.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we’re humble
and add to the peace of the congregation,

00:47:46.179 --> 00:47:48.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
we make Jehovah happy.

00:47:49.316 --> 00:47:51.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
As Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:47:51.318 --> 00:47:55.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
we cherish our privilege
to share the good news with others.

00:47:55.889 --> 00:47:59.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
What can help us
be adaptable in our ministry?

