00:48:24.184 --> 00:48:26.520 line:10% position:50% align:center
is when I’ve prepared an introduction

00:48:26.520 --> 00:48:28.555 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I’ve planned the conversation

00:48:28.555 --> 00:48:32.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
but the householder doesn’t follow the plan

00:48:32.125 --> 00:48:34.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I have to adapt.

00:48:34.828 --> 00:48:37.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever had that experience?

00:48:37.230 --> 00:48:41.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
This could mean
that what we prepared just won’t work.

00:48:42.803 --> 00:48:45.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we are going to discuss four tips

00:48:45.806 --> 00:48:48.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
that have helped me and hopefully

00:48:48.642 --> 00:48:51.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
will help you be more adaptable.

00:48:52.045 --> 00:48:54.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
The four tips are

00:48:54.214 --> 00:48:57.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) know your territory,

00:48:58.418 --> 00:49:02.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) make use of the Teaching Toolbox,

00:49:03.690 --> 00:49:06.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
(3) anticipate

00:49:06.526 --> 00:49:09.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
common objections or questions,

00:49:09.896 --> 00:49:12.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
and (4) be flexible

00:49:12.933 --> 00:49:15.902 line:90% position:50% align:center
and adjust to the householder’s needs,

00:49:15.902 --> 00:49:20.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
because remember,
this is meant to be a conversation,

00:49:20.107 --> 00:49:23.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
not a sermon or a sales pitch.

00:49:25.245 --> 00:49:27.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, let’s look at a situation

00:49:27.414 --> 00:49:31.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
where applying
these four suggestions can help.

00:49:36.857 --> 00:49:38.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what introduction are you using?

00:49:38.959 --> 00:49:41.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
I thought I would talk
about economic problems.

00:49:41.962 --> 00:49:43.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm.
Good idea!

00:49:43.430 --> 00:49:44.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
It really suits the territory.

00:49:44.898 --> 00:49:46.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks.

00:49:46.199 --> 00:49:51.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ll read Isaiah 65:21-23
and then offer the <i>Kingdom</i>  tract.

00:49:51.204 --> 00:49:52.239 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perfect.

00:49:52.239 --> 00:49:53.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ll get the scripture ready.

00:49:54.207 --> 00:49:55.375 line:90% position:50% align:center
Excellent.

00:50:06.253 --> 00:50:07.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
Good morning.

00:50:08.422 --> 00:50:12.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many people in our area
struggle to make ends meet.

00:50:12.125 --> 00:50:14.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you think there will ever be a time

00:50:14.161 --> 00:50:16.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we won’t have to stress about money?

00:50:16.797 --> 00:50:19.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
Actually, now isn’t a good time.

00:50:19.666 --> 00:50:21.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just received some bad news.

00:50:22.636 --> 00:50:24.337 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sorry.

00:50:24.337 --> 00:50:26.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll come back another time then.

00:50:26.573 --> 00:50:27.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:50:32.846 --> 00:50:34.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:50:34.181 --> 00:50:38.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our sister applied
our first two tips really well.

00:50:38.852 --> 00:50:42.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
But our sisters are usually excellent
when it comes to the ministry

00:50:42.823 --> 00:50:45.625 line:90% position:50% align:center
so no real surprises there.

00:50:45.625 --> 00:50:47.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you notice?

00:50:47.260 --> 00:50:50.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, she knew her territory well

00:50:50.630 --> 00:50:55.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
and had a presentation
designed specifically for it.

00:50:55.602 --> 00:50:59.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second, her scripture and talking point

00:50:59.106 --> 00:51:03.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
were taken from the tract
<i>What Is the Kingdom of God?,</i>

00:51:03.610 --> 00:51:07.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
which, as you know,
is part of our Teaching Toolbox.

00:51:07.380 --> 00:51:12.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, when the householder
had something else on her mind,

00:51:12.052 --> 00:51:15.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
our sister opted to return later.

00:51:15.622 --> 00:51:19.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
That could be a good decision
in this kind of situation,

00:51:19.893 --> 00:51:22.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
but let’s see what would happen

00:51:22.696 --> 00:51:25.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
if she were to ask just one more question

00:51:25.866 --> 00:51:29.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
and adapt according
to the householder’s response.

00:51:31.905 --> 00:51:34.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
Actually, now isn’t a good time.

00:51:34.708 --> 00:51:37.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just received some bad news.

00:51:37.878 --> 00:51:39.346 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sorry.

00:51:39.346 --> 00:51:41.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there anything we can do to help?

00:51:42.482 --> 00:51:43.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:51:44.518 --> 00:51:48.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
I, uh, I- I just heard
that my sister has cancer.

00:51:48.989 --> 00:51:52.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, that must be so difficult

00:51:52.425 --> 00:51:53.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
for your sister

00:51:53.660 --> 00:51:55.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
and for you!

00:51:56.062 --> 00:51:59.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, when someone we love is suffering,
we can often feel helpless.

00:51:59.266 --> 00:52:01.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s exactly how I feel.

00:52:01.268 --> 00:52:02.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you have a moment,

00:52:02.702 --> 00:52:05.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
could I show you something
that I find comforting

00:52:05.839 --> 00:52:09.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
about a time in the near future
when our loved ones will never suffer again?

00:52:09.709 --> 00:52:11.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm, I’d like that.

00:52:11.111 --> 00:52:13.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice what the Bible says

00:52:13.413 --> 00:52:17.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Revelation 21:3, 4:

00:52:17.751 --> 00:52:20.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With that I heard a loud voice
from the throne say . . .”

00:52:24.357 --> 00:52:26.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wow!

00:52:26.193 --> 00:52:30.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you see how she was able
to offer this woman real comfort

00:52:30.797 --> 00:52:33.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
just by being adaptable?

00:52:33.700 --> 00:52:37.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
All it took was one simple question,

00:52:37.437 --> 00:52:40.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is there anything we can do to help?

00:52:40.207 --> 00:52:44.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
She was sincere and friendly,
and the householder responded.

00:52:44.978 --> 00:52:49.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
At that point,
our sister applied our third tip.

00:52:49.249 --> 00:52:53.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
She obviously was familiar
with some common anxieties

00:52:53.286 --> 00:52:55.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
of ones in that territory

00:52:55.455 --> 00:52:58.091 line:90% position:50% align:center
because she smoothly transitioned

00:52:58.091 --> 00:53:02.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the topic of suffering,
which allowed her to listen

00:53:02.329 --> 00:53:05.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the householder’s real concern

00:53:05.498 --> 00:53:09.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then implement our fourth tip.

00:53:09.502 --> 00:53:12.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
She adjusted to meet those needs.

00:53:12.906 --> 00:53:16.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
Plus, she didn’t struggle
to find information to use.

00:53:16.643 --> 00:53:20.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
She stayed right there
in her Teaching Toolbox.

00:53:21.481 --> 00:53:25.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
Granted, not every situation
will be as straightforward as this,

00:53:25.685 --> 00:53:27.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it takes time and experience

00:53:27.988 --> 00:53:31.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get comfortable moving
from one topic to another.

00:53:31.925 --> 00:53:34.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
But if we apply our four tips:

00:53:34.828 --> 00:53:37.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
know your territory,

00:53:37.631 --> 00:53:41.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
make use of the Teaching Toolbox,

00:53:41.368 --> 00:53:45.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
try to anticipate
common objections or questions,

00:53:45.372 --> 00:53:48.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then adjust to the householder’s needs,

00:53:48.942 --> 00:53:50.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
by applying these,

00:53:50.944 --> 00:53:55.548 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’ll find very quickly
that we are having meaningful conversations

00:53:55.548 --> 00:53:58.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
and are able to share targeted truths

00:53:58.652 --> 00:54:01.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
with those most in need.

00:54:02.689 --> 00:54:06.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
As always, these are just a few techniques

00:54:06.126 --> 00:54:08.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
that have worked for me,

00:54:08.528 --> 00:54:11.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I hope they work for you.

00:54:11.231 --> 00:54:15.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, part of the beauty of our ministry

00:54:15.468 --> 00:54:19.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
is that we continue to sharpen one another.

00:54:21.174 --> 00:54:23.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
What good suggestions! 

00:54:23.843 --> 00:54:28.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this example,
the sister was able to start a conversation

00:54:28.381 --> 00:54:31.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
with a simple “good morning.”

00:54:31.251 --> 00:54:35.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, in real life,
the way you greet people in your territory

00:54:35.522 --> 00:54:38.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
might be different
than what we saw in the video.

00:54:39.993 --> 00:54:42.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
We hope you’ve enjoyed this month’s theme,

00:54:42.662 --> 00:54:45.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Make Wise Decisions.”

00:54:45.365 --> 00:54:47.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
Before we conclude,

00:54:47.367 --> 00:54:50.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’d like to introduce you
to our brothers and sisters

00:54:50.503 --> 00:54:53.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
living in a land rich in Bible history

00:54:53.773 --> 00:54:55.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Greece!

00:54:55.775 --> 00:54:58.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
Greece is a mountainous country,

00:54:58.278 --> 00:55:01.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
located at the southernmost part

00:55:01.181 --> 00:55:02.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Balkan peninsula,

00:55:02.749 --> 00:55:05.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
with a rugged and diverse landscape.

00:55:05.552 --> 00:55:09.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
It also includes more than 2,000 islands.

00:55:09.255 --> 00:55:12.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
And with one of the longest coastlines

00:55:12.959 --> 00:55:16.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
in all of Europe,
this is a land of beautiful beaches

00:55:16.696 --> 00:55:19.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
and sheltered coves.

00:55:19.766 --> 00:55:24.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
Greece is known for its classic
Mediterranean cuisine and delicacies

00:55:24.804 --> 00:55:29.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
like <i>moussaka,</i> made from eggplant,

00:55:29.142 --> 00:55:32.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
and <i>dolmadakia,</i> stuffed grape leaves

00:55:32.445 --> 00:55:35.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
usually filled with rice and herbs.

00:55:35.015 --> 00:55:38.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
A less familiar part of the Greek diet

00:55:38.284 --> 00:55:41.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
is Chios mastiha,
or mastic gum,

00:55:41.821 --> 00:55:44.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
which is made from the sap of a tree

00:55:44.491 --> 00:55:47.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
grown only on the small island of Chios.

00:55:47.627 --> 00:55:51.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
In ancient times,
people chewed mastic to freshen their breath;

00:55:51.698 --> 00:55:54.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
it was an early version of chewing gum.

00:55:54.968 --> 00:55:57.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, it’s typically used

00:55:57.604 --> 00:56:00.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
to flavor everything from bread to ice cream.

00:56:02.042 --> 00:56:06.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
The preaching of the good news in Greece
goes all the way back to the first century,

00:56:06.713 --> 00:56:08.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
when the apostle Paul

00:56:08.581 --> 00:56:10.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
first “[stepped] over into Macedonia.”

00:56:10.950 --> 00:56:14.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
He landed in the seaport town of Neapolis,

00:56:14.220 --> 00:56:17.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
known today as the city of Kavála.

00:56:17.690 --> 00:56:20.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the preaching in Kavála

00:56:20.293 --> 00:56:23.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
is still going strong,
with four congregations

00:56:23.463 --> 00:56:26.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
busy with public witnessing

00:56:26.132 --> 00:56:28.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
throughout the city,
including at the harbor

00:56:28.935 --> 00:56:30.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
and at rest areas.

00:56:30.703 --> 00:56:32.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
Kavála’s old city

00:56:32.705 --> 00:56:34.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
is built on a hill,

00:56:34.441 --> 00:56:36.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
where brothers and sisters

00:56:36.576 --> 00:56:40.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
often climb many steep steps
to reach the homes in their territory.

00:56:41.548 --> 00:56:45.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
The branch office in Greece
oversees the activity

00:56:45.718 --> 00:56:47.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
of more than 30,000 publishers,

00:56:47.921 --> 00:56:50.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
including 2,900

00:56:50.457 --> 00:56:53.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the neighboring island nation of Cyprus.

00:56:53.526 --> 00:56:58.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
They preach to a population
of about 11 million people,

00:56:58.231 --> 00:57:01.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
often in some of the very same cities

00:57:01.267 --> 00:57:03.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
where Paul preached in the first century,

00:57:03.403 --> 00:57:08.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
including Thessalonica,
or modern-day Thessaloníki;

00:57:08.441 --> 00:57:10.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
Beroea, or Véroia;

00:57:10.977 --> 00:57:13.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the capital city of Athens.

00:57:13.413 --> 00:57:17.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll end our visit to Greece
back in Macedonia,

00:57:17.617 --> 00:57:19.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
where our Greek brothers and sisters

00:57:19.719 --> 00:57:24.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
send their warmest greetings
from the Assembly Hall in Thessaloníki.

00:57:25.258 --> 00:57:29.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:57:29.062 --> 00:57:31.931 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

